Comment: Interesting problem and conjecture!
You could say if the upper limit is inclusive or not. Maybe you could also give tests and validators to check if this was understood correctly.

My solution in Python:

limit = int(input())
memo = {1:1}
def c(k):
    if k in memo:
        return memo[k]
    if k % 2 == 0:
        l = 1 + c(k//2)
    else:
        l = 1 + c(3*k+1)
    memo[k] = l
    return l
print(*max(
    ((n,c(n)) for n in range(1,limit)),
    key = lambda p:p[1]
))
